FBIS4-45241 "jptdd023__l94085" JPRS-TDD-94-023-L JPRS Narcotics 16 May 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY Dutch Citizen Arrested at Istanbul Airport With Over 12 Kg Dutch Citizen Arrested at Istanbul Airport With Over 12 Kg of Heroin NC2605133894 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 16 May 94 p 3 NC2605133894 Istanbul HURRIYET Turkish BFN [Report by Rauf Gerz: "Dogs Found 12 Kg of Heroin"] [Text] Some 12.345 kg of heroin were discovered on Dutchman Johannes Dijkstra at the Ataturk Airport in Istanbul. The drug trafficker reportedly revealed that he charged the dispatchers of the heroin double the amount usually paid to couriers because the airport police have begun to use dogs, which can sniff and detect narcotics. The police searched Dijkstra and his suitcase when he arrived at the airport at 0630. They discovered 12.345 kg of heroin in 12 packages in his possession.
